ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Has your child had any recent injuries or illnesses
Recently seen a doctor or medical professional for any reason?
Has your child started any new treatments
Is your child taking any new medications (over the counter or prescription)
Insomnia: Have you had any problems with falling asleep, staying asleep, or waking up too early? (Severe = sleep time disrupted more than 3 hours most nights).
Tired during the day, wants to nap, sleepy
Weight Gain: Have you had any problems with weight gain? (Severe = new clothes required)
Seeing or hearing things that are not there
Oppositionality (refusing to do what is asked)
Aggression. Verbal threats or physical aggression directed towards others.
Notes: 0 = NOT PRESENT; 1 = MILD (no interference with functioning; 2 = MODERATE (interference in at least one area of functioning); 3 = SEVERE (prevents functioning in at least one area, or is a major threat to health)

ElementDescription: Loses temper easily, short fuse, Impatient
Summary Chart: Injury (most serious) - specify other injury
Have there been any changes in eating habits since the last session? (specify)

Specify change in significant family events
